omori is possibly my favorite game i have ever played. the story, oh the story where do i even get started. just, play the game for yourself. the price is so worth it, though i originally got it on the switch i was interested if my gameplay would be any different. and so far, it has been! ultimately, it would be a long time to read everything i have to say about this game. the guide book is very helpful as well for new players and older fans as well! when i got mine in the mail and started to read, there were things even i didnt know! (i have about 500 hours on the switch plus hours of research. i know, a waste of my life.) blackspace though its meant for the repressed memories hidden away for sunny to forget, is meant to be dark.. though yet there are some jokes in there that unexpected such as encountering omoli. though you must do a specific task before being able to talk to him it ends up (in my opinion) being perfect.

the story is about a boy named sunny, a hikkiomori who is moving away in three days, you have the option to either stay as a shut in or go out and connect with your friends, attempting to make up the past 4 years you have been staying inside. after a tragic accident it scarred him so he resorted to bottling up his feeling and sleeping and having dreams about before the incident happened. Most of the game takes place in headspace. i cant explain more than this before i start bringing up other topics. just play the game.
